
// The code demonstrates the use of the [if] slot in Hyperlambda. It evaluates a boolean condition and, if true, executes the lambda object within the [.lambda] node. In this example, if the condition is true, it sets the value of the [.result] node to "Yes". The [set-value] slot is used to update the node's value based on the condition's outcome.
if
   .:bool:true
   .lambda
      set-value:x:@.result
         .:Yes
